<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-1944] isCase implementation for BigDecimals needed based on numerical value only</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-1944</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;BigDecimals carry both a numerical value and a precision (scale).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Groovy, when BigDecimals are compared, only the numerical value is taken into account, but isCase() uses both value and scale.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be consistent.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;assert 0.5 == 0.50000  // works&lt;br/&gt;
switch(0.5) {&lt;br/&gt;
  case 0.50000: println &quot;match&quot; // doesn&apos;t match&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
